This paper deals with the issue of physical layer security in wireless relay networks, which is a topic related to information theory (cs.IT) and network infrastructure (cs.NI). The paper also discusses mechanisms to incentivize relays to report their true private channel information, which is a topic related to game theory (cs.GT) and distributed computing (cs.DC). Additionally, the paper addresses the issue of eavesdropping, which is a topic related to computer security (cs.CR).
